g.text: Problem: Powering Hummus with Data about Accounts
Weâ€™d like to build a system that pulls in information related to user identities from many
different third party SaaS applications like Slack, Zoom, Asana, JIRA, PagerDuty, Google Workspace, GitHub, Slack, etc. and reconciles them into a single up-to-date representation.
* someone in IT can see who has what (read only)
** create a web ui view to view this data
** per domain (customer) multiple apps and integrations
Specifically, we are interested in consolidating these data fields below from different sources into a single unified view.
* Accounts. i.e. alice@hummus.com on Slack, or bob@hummus.com on Twitter. (semi slow)
* Groups. Collections of users within a third party application. (slowly changing)
* Permissions. e.g. admin role / read-only role. (slowly changing)
* Last Sign In. i.e. the date of when a user last used the service).
* Latency: hourly or daily updates of this information, does not need 100-250 ms real uptime view
* view piece should aim to load / render information in 100-250 ms
* 10,000,000 total integrations across all customers (5 groups per employees, 1 permission per employee, last_sign_in)
2. Given a user, look at the user table to see if there's a match by email
3. If there's no match, skip over the user not existsant
4. If there's a match by email
* go pull all company_integration / user_id entries,
* IT admin consistent views as much as possible
